'''最高指导原则'''（{{Lang-en|Prime Directive}}），也被称之为“星际舰队通用法令一号（{{lang|en|Starfleet General Order 1}}）”、“通用法令一号（{{lang|en|General Order 1}}）”和“非干涉原则（{{lang|en|Non-Interference Directive}}）”，是“[[星艦奇航記|星际迷航]][[虛構世界|虚拟宇宙]]”中[[星际舰队|星际舰队]]的指导原则，其内容在于禁止星际舰队成员干涉外星文明的内在和自然发展。<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web |author1=Janet D. Stemwedel |title=The Philosophy Of Star Trek: Is The Prime Directive Ethical? |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/janetstemwedel/2015/08/20/the-philosophy-of-star-trek-is-the-prime-directive-ethical/ |publisher=[[福布斯|福布斯]] |accessdate=2019-06-17 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109042736/https://www.forbes.com/sites/janetstemwedel/2015/08/20/the-philosophy-of-star-trek-is-the-prime-directive-ethical/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>最高指导原则特别适用于那些[[科学|科学]]、[[技术|技术]]和[[文化|文化]]发展低于某个阈值的外星文明，以防止[[星舰|星舰]]成员利用其技术优势将自己的[[价值观|价值观]]或理想强加给他们。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Richard J. Peltz |title=On a Wagon Train to Afghanistan: Limitations on Star Trek's Prime Directive |journal=University of Arkansas at Little Rock Law Review |date=2003 |volume=25 |issue=3 |page=635 |url=https://lawrepository.ualr.edu/lawreview/vol25/iss3/6/ |accessdate=2019-06-17 |author= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617103823/https://lawrepository.ualr.edu/lawreview/vol25/iss3/6/ |archive-date=2019-06-17 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>最高指导原则自从在《[[星際爭霸戰|星际旅行：初代]]》第一季中被提出以来，就一直受到许多星际旅行的粉丝的关注并在后续剧集中引发讨论。

== 术语定义 ==
尽管“最高指导原则”被诸多“[[星际旅行|星际旅行]]”的角色在电视剧或真人电影中提及和引用，但该原则的实际内容却从未真正展示给观众。<ref name="Fariver">{{cite web |author1=Cyrus Farivar |title=Why Star Trek’s Prime Directive could never be enforced |url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/09/why-star-treks-prime-directive-could-never-be-enforced/ |publisher=[[Ars_Technica|科技艺术]] |accessdate=2019-06-17 |archive-date=2021-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305230038/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/09/why-star-treks-prime-directive-could-never-be-enforced/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>对于该原则的最完整定义来自非[[星际旅行正典|正典]]作品，这包括：
{{Cquote|最高指导原则禁止星际舰队人员或航天器干扰任何社会的自然发展；并强制要求星际舰队的船只和船员都是可以牺牲的，以防止违反这一原则。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Michael Okuda |author2=Denise Okuda |author3=Debbie Mirek |title=The Star Trek Encyclopedia |date=2011 |publisher=Simon and Schuster |isbn=9781451646887 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cbYf2l7gczUC |accessdate=2019-06-17}}</ref>}}
和
{{Cquote|每一个种族都有权在其本有的文化下进化，星际舰队的任何下属星舰或个人都不得影响外星种族进化过程、文化、制度、生活方式，影响的方式包括给予外星种族更先进的知识和科技。在拯救外星种族生命或其船只时也决不许违反最高指导原则，除非被拯救的种族已经受到了其他文明污染。最高指导原则高于其他任何原则，星际舰队下属星舰和个人必须将其视为最高原则。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Bernard E. Menke |author2=Rick D. Stuart |title=The Federation |date=1986 |publisher=McGraw-Hill |isbn=9780931787300 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S9_4PAAACAAJ |accessdate=2019-06-17}}</ref>}}

== 发展过程 ==
最高指导原则的创立通常归功于《[[星际旅行：初代|星际旅行：初代]]》的的制作人{{Link-en|吉恩·库恩|Gene L. Coon}}。<ref>{{cite book |author1=Edward Gross |author2=Mark A. Altman |title=The Fifty-Year Mission: The Next 25 Years: From The Next Generation to J. J. Abrams: The Complete, Uncensored, and Unauthorized Oral History of Star Trek |date=2016 |publisher=Macmillan |isbn=9781250089472 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wzuKCwAAQBAJ |accessdate=2019-06-17 |archive-date=2019-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819175412/https://books.google.com/books?id=wzuKCwAAQBAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Scott Collura |title=Shatner: Creator Gene Roddenberry 'Had Little to Do with Star Trek' After First 13 Episodes |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/21/shatner-creator-gene-roddenberry-had-little-to-do-with-star-trek-after-first-13-episodes |publisher=[[IGN|IGN]] |accessdate=2019-06-17 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111214011/https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/21/shatner-creator-gene-roddenberry-had-little-to-do-with-star-trek-after-first-13-episodes |dead-url=no }}</ref>最高指导原则反应了当代的政治观点，即[[越南战争|越南战争]]是[[超级大国|超级大国]]对[[东南亚|东南亚]]社会的一种干涉；而最高指导原则的创立被认为是对这种事务的反对。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=H. Bruce Franklin |title=Star Trek in the Vietnam Era |journal=Science Fiction Studies |date=1994-03 |volume=21 |issue=62 |url=https://www.depauw.edu/sfs/backissues/62/franklin62art.htm |accessdate=2019-06-17 |archive-date=2021-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219213358/https://www.depauw.edu/sfs/backissues/62/franklin62art.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Patrick McCormick |title=Final frontier covers old ground |journal=U.S. Catholic |date=1996-03 |volume=61 |issue=3 |pages=46,48 |accessdate=2019-06-17}}</ref>

